<div class="left-col">
  <h2 class="content-heading">Hover Effects</h2>
  <p>JBC comes with awesome wrapper for your links with images for great hover effects. This wrapper do everyhting for you, it will automatically add all neccessary code inside of the link depending on kind of this link. Let's see on examples:</p>
  <p>For example if you have the link with image which will <strong>open popup window with content</strong>, then it will look like these ones:</p>
  <p><a href="folio/folio1.php" class="popup imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-1.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a> <a data-title="You can add some description" href="folio/folio1.php" class="popup2 imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-2.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a></p>
  <p>If you have the link with image which will <strong>open popup window with image</strong>, then it will look like these ones:</p>
  <p><a href="images/demo/1.jpg" class="pop-image imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-1.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a> <a data-title="You can add some description" href="images/demo/1.jpg" class="pop-image2 imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-2.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a></p>
  <p>If you have the <strong>inner Ajax link</strong> with image, then it will look like these ones:</p>
  <p><a href="?page=home" class="ajax imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-1.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a> <a data-title="You can add some description" href="?page=home" class="ajax2 imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-2.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a></p>
  <p>Or you have the <strong>external link</strong> to some website, then it will look like these ones:</p>
  <p><a href="http://www.idangero.us" target="_blank" class="imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-1.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a> <a data-title="You can add some description" href="http://www.idangero.us" target="_blank" class="imageLink"><img src="images/folio/260-2.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a></p>
  <p>And the final type of link is used (and will work) ONLY in portfolio to<strong> open new content section</strong>, it will look like these ones:</p>
  <p><a href="folio/folio1.php" class="imageLink open-item"><img src="images/folio/260-1.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a> <a data-title="You can add some description" href="folio/folio1.php" class="imageLink open-item"><img src="images/folio/260-2.jpg" width="260" height="180" alt=" " /></a></p>
</div>

